.<br>
<br>
Previously, I was using a FB in the main hand for aggro.  Once I got the yak, I put it in the main hand with the ribcracker in the offhand.<br>
<br>
This weapon beats the ever living crap out of the FB for aggro.  Initially, I was in a group with an enchanter, who was 70% slowing.  I had maxed out dex, which obviously helps on procs.<br>
<br>
I was there for roughly 2 hours and lost aggro ONCE.  That's right, ONCE.  There were points I was actually not even using taunt or disarm.  Just plodding along with attack and kick.  No aggro loss whatsoever.  When the yak proc'ed, there was absolutely nothing that would pull it off.<br>
<br>
Couple this with a FB in the off hand and it's even better.  <br>
